# Weekly Retrospective
This week has been quite productive and blessed with these rains! I created this blog website, deep-dived into Linux kernel internals, and focused on the RoDevSy project.

### Technical Progress
- **RoDevSy:** Added a database backup cron job to ensure data reliability.
- **Blog:** Created this blog website in SvelteKit 5 using MDsveX for markdown processing, Shiki for syntax code highlighting, and the static adapter for SSG.

### Academic Check-in (FAST)
- **Coursework:** Midterm OS and DB lab exams finished. Extremely easy.
- **Books:** Focusing on the OS book; it is an absolute gem.

### Key Learning
- This week I learned that at the end of the day, foundational knowledge is what makes you stand out from others.

