# Weekly Prospective
Next week will be the week of CI/CD pipeline setup using either Jenkins (which I don't think I should, but I will look at the trade-offs) or GitHub Actions. Right now, I'm manually fetching the GitHub repo, building it on the VPS, and hosting it on an HTTP port. Extremely stupid. I'll now configure it to create images on a Docker Registry, which are then pulled by the VPS and restarted automatically.

### Primary Goals
- [ ] **RoDevSy:** Successfully implement and test the CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions and a Docker Registry.
- [ ] **University:** Complete the upcoming reading assignments for OS and start preparing for the next wave of database projects.
- [ ] **Blog:** 
  - Write and publish a detailed post about my migration from Next.js to SvelteKit 5 and why it was the right move.
  - A post on why Remote Functions are bad and why you should avoid it in Roblox. How to use Remote Events efficiently.
  - A post on Client-Server model of Roblox. How Network Ownership of model works.
